Author: MiBambino
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: I had an idea to boost the values of both coins:  First, have both of them support the other. The lottery can be done with both mne and art, the fees for the world app could be paid in both coins, buying a genesis address in mne, paying for the token creation service in 1000 art, ...  But, what I think is a good idea, is having the ICO marketplace also be an exchange only for tokens created with the minereum creation service (like the 300 coin). The creators of those coins could pay a monthly fee of 500mne or 50.000art, launch their ICO for 1000mne or 100.000art, transaction fees could be paid in art and mne, ...  Basically they could create an entire ecosystem for us to create coins at a much cheaper price AND instantly list them on an exchange. By paying monthly fees you ensure the demand and volume stay high, plus its easier for smaller companies to pay monthly than to pay a larger amount for listing up front, like with other exchanges.

Author: MiBambino
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: No I'm not, I'm just an investor who gets insanely mad reading shit from FUD spreaders like you. I can't tell you how many of you I've seen come and go over the last months, with every single coin imaginable. I saw guys like you claiming NEO was a pyramid scheme, how ETH was on the brink of bancrupty, how the developer of LTC had killed himself, ... and it drives me mad beyond belief. Answer me this, what do you have to gain from acting the way you do? I'm trying to remain positive by giving ideas to the devs on how to approach this situation, how to broaden their market, how to have both coins work together and profit from each other, and then pieces of shit like you come here trying to drive prices down. I've never talked shit about a coin I didn't care about. Never. I simply let it be. Yet you and those other retards are constantly posting shit here, claiming both projects are scams. Why? People like you don't strike me as 'moral', so I sincerely doubt you're spreading FUD here to 'help investors keep their money'. You rather strike me as the type of people who're trying to accumulate more by driving prices down. Earlier you said you owned a bunch of Artemine addresses. Tell me, how did the situation change? Yes, I've seen people like you, trying to shake down the markets to grab whatever the weakest hands drop, claiming to be moral. Last questions, do you believe in Jesus? Are you a proud gun-wielding american? Did you vote for trump? Do you think climate change is a hoax? Judging from the way you took 1 random guy's claims about a corrupt dev trying to scam everyone when there's literally no proof for that, accepting it blindly as facts because it fits your agenda, you'll answer 'yes' on all questions.

Author: MiBambino
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: You can't sell the entire address on bittrex, but you can sell your coins every day. I'm afraid however that 1.000 ART won't make you much money. I think ART could go to 10$, but with 1.000ART you'd still only mine about 0.04 of them, which gives you about 40 cents a day (1.000ART = 10MNE = 12$). You'd ofcourse be making profits after 1 month, adding up to about 12$ a month.  Now, in the first quarter of 2018 you'll be able to sell the entire address on a special Artemine platform. If we compare it to selling a business, you should be able to sell it for the gross revenue of 1 year, which is about 12$*12 months, so 144$ or about 0.5ETH.  I recommend you buy some more Art so that you can get a better income. Personally I've bought 10.000 so that, if my prediction comes true and ART gets valued at 10$, I make about 4$ a day, which comes down to about 1440$ a year in passive income.  It's still a question on what the purpose of ART will be for an investor. If it's not gonna do anything it's not gonna be worth 10$, not even 1$. I think they should integrate it with the lottery and the world app, but that's just my 2 cents

Author: artemine
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: Hi All,  We will burn the first received MNEs in the ICO in the next few days! The received MNEs are currently worth around $1 Million (~50% of MNE's supply).  https://etherscan.io/token/0x1a95b271b0535d15fa49932daba31ba612b52946?a=0xcf24fa5606bbe4dab3ba24cb586b4353fe83094a  The ICO will continue as normal and we will periodically burn the next received tokens.  The MNEs will be sent to the Minereum Token Creation Service (will be automatically burned) and an Ethereum Token will be generated out of it.  We may use this created token just for Minereum/Artemine fans, we are not sure yet.  We may create a vote here on bitcointalk for the community to decide what to do with it, after all, the creation of this token will be worth about $1 Million.  More updates soon, stay tuned!

Author: Tonton99
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: Have you all noticed that the Mne donations for the ICO has come to a hold. Only 500 MNE has been converted since day 1 ended and the last one 6 hours ago. Besides, the MNE converted to ART are already taken off the market no matter if they are burned yet. Under normal circumstances those will not hit the market anymore. I see some huge buy orders on MNE sub 0.0003 so the speculators are waiting for the price to go down < $1 to accumulate a lot of MNE for future gains.  I keep following this ICO with great interest since this provides a good learning opportunity on the dynamics when Alts are subject to donations for ICO's. There is so much speculation going on and so much uncertainty that the market sometimes reacts completely adverse to expectation. It also appears that most investors have no clue in what they are investing, they only see an opportunity for quick gains or the deep desire to hold a genesis account once in their lives. There is also so much kept in the dark like someone holding > 300 inactive genesis accounts on MNE that were all of a sudden released into ART genesis accounts minutes before the day 1 deadline closed. It's 100% sure those addresses belong to one and the same person that now holds the same amount of genesis accounts on both coins. He can start mining both MNE and ART while the MNE investors face the risk that the accumulation of the supply will go much faster now that all those accounts are revealed as active. I have some serious doubts whether the original MNE airdrop was played fair and square when someone managed to acquire so many genesis accounts and kept those inactive for such a long time (May-September). It feels that the investor is always 2 plays behind in the game when there is so much manipulation going on.  Good thing is that MNE is cheap now so who likes to gamble can stack 10k supply and wait for it to triple in value to sell it off, rinse repeat. Don't hodll since you never know who is really in control of your money.

Author: den_penta
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: Hugh! They change (add new info) whitepaper today! And this is new information about total amount and WTF is 'PublicMining'.  4. Circulating Supply The circulating supply of Artemine is defined by the formula: [GenesisAddressMining] + [PublicMining] [GenesisAddressMining] The initial circulating supply of Artemine will be defined by the amount of participants on the contribution phase and by the total amount of ARTE they will hold on each Genesis Address, the circulating supply will then increase on each ethereum block by the rate defined previously in the section 2.3. As an example if we have a total of 5,000 Genesis Addresses created in the contribution phase and each of them with 10,000 ARTE the circulating supply generated on each ethereum block will be: (5000 * 10000) * 0.00000001 = 0.5 ARTE. Taking into account the current average block of ethereum of 20 seconds that would produce the following amount of ARTE per day: 0.5 x 4320 = 2160 ARTE.

Author: Nixzor
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: MNE has a fully functional ETH token creation service based on smart-contract (no programming knowledge required, just complete a form). You have to send 1 MNE that will be BURNED.  ARTE is the next step. It is an ICO creation service, still backed up by smart contracts and by burning the required ARTE to create ICO. By making ICOs in smart contract form, there can not be any more ICO scams.  So the tokens go hand-in-hand. With one you make an ETH token and with the other you make the ICO for it. There is no limited supply as coins are burned so the developer made the "genesis self mining" adresses for both coins.  MNE can be also a business opportunity, I know a high-school student that made aprox 0.5 BTC by "creating your own token for you". He was just using the MNE token creation service while people didn't knew about.  Later edit: Now is the time that everyone tweets about this ICO with the #artemine and #arte tags to raise awareness. Remember that it is in your best interest to spread the word of Artemine to your friends or in your bitcointalk signature.

Body: The whitepaper is a joke, not going to argue with that! The reason I invested so much money into MNE and ARTE is because the whitepaper was such dogshit that I had to post a series of questions with the dev on the MNE forum about a month ago. Sorry if I come across defensive I just don't want to see an avalanche of unjust criticism when it seems like the dev is just really overworked.  If I REALLY REALLY had to guess, I would say the dev understands the clock is ticking and this concept with be cloned with other projects and he wants to get out there FIRST.

Author: ZenFr
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: ARTEMINE ICO will start on september 14 at 17 h UTC (19 h for France). The ICO will run 30 days.  It is a "first day ICO" because this day you have a 400% bonus (1000 ARTE vs. 250 at the ICO end). Quote Exchange rates    1 ETH (+/- 300 USD)    10 MNE (+/- 50 USD)                Day 1    1000 ARTE    1000 ARTE   Day 2 - Day 10    667 ARTE     500 ARTE Day 11 - Day 19    500 ARTE     333 ARTE Day 20 - Day 25    400 ARTE     286 ARTE Day 26 - Day 30    333 ARTE     250 ARTE  Note : 1000 Arte (1 ETH or 10 MNE first day ICO) are mining 0.0432 ARTE/day. Then, for all time holder, 240 MNE will buy 24.000 ARTE who are mining 24 x 0.0432 ARTE = 1,0368 ARTEMINE each day.

Author: artemine
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: Hi Everyone,  The start of the ICO is only few hours away, we would like to provide few more details about it:  1. Start Time  As already announced, the ICO will start at 5 PM UTC (Today, September 14).  To be sure about the timing you can check the counter on our website on the top right corner: http://artemine.org/  2. Minimum Amounts allowed in the ICO  ETH: 0.1 MNE: 10  3. Transactions  For participants on the ICO all they will have to do is to send a simple ETH or MNE transaction to the ICO Address that we will post when the ICO is live.  4. Genesis Addresses Generation  All participants will have the address from where they sent the ETH or MNE converted into a ARTE Genesis Address (All addresses will be generated after the ICO).  -> DO NOT send coins to the ICO Address from exchanges like kraken, poloniex, etc.  For transparency, all the Genesis Addresses along with the attributed ARTE will be visible on this page:  http://genesis.artemine.org/  The page will be updated in real time.

Author: MiBambino
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: I understand. People can say all they want how 'this project is incredible' and 'the devs always deliver', but guess what that's not enough. Every single day a new coin or ICO is born and the ones that make it are the ones that advertise and scream out to the world why we should buy them; they run bounty campaigns, they have paid facebook ads, they write articles, they're active on social media, they communicate, they have pre-ico sales, they provide intrinsic value to their tokens. Minereum/artemine simply don't do any of that. If a coin isn't used or demanded a lot, it's not scarce. If it's not scarce, there's literally no reason for it to gain in value. Again, people say 'oh the value will go to the moon once the mne coins get burned' guess what, the coins aren't in circulation anymore if you buy and hold. We need a ton of people using them, and I don't see how that's gonna happen if barely anyone knows the ICO is even happening tomorrow, and if they don't innovate and provide us with a decent roadmap. I could write their whitepaper in less than an hour, because it's shit. I believe in the products, I just don't believe in the devs anymore to pull it off. The only reason why I'm not selling with 200% profits right now is because I believe in miracles and because I want nothing more than to be proven wrong

Author: snodo
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: MNE and ARTE are tokens built on the ethereum network. These tokens are called ERC20 tokens. When someone develops an ERC20 token, this token will get an address in the network (the custom token address) - the token is not identified by its name but by its custom token address.  MNE is one ERC20 token. ARTE will be another ERC20 token. So ARTE will of course have its own custom token address.  Because these ERC20 tokens are base on the ethereum network, these tokens can be stored in ethereum wallets. MyEtherWallet is an ethererum wallet, so you can store your MNE / ARTE / every other ERC20 token there.

Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: The Self-Mining principle relies on the basis that the Token will mine the coins itself for a specific amount of time without the direct need of Mining Equipment or Miners. The token supply is automatically generated on the fly by a mathematical formula.

Author: breezeattack
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: Correct. You need ETH miners for the self mining smart contract to work. So it's really not energy/resources efficient, in fact, it's less so than any-other coin that distributes all of their coins at the start. Artemine is really the least eco friendly ETH based token since you constantly need ETH miners for the self mining of the coin. A self mining coin does have it's benefits though, such as incentivising people to hold the coin vs sale it since you can always mine more coins. Not sure if that's a must buy feature though.

Author: LouTong
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: also...  please correct me if i'm using bad maths or logic but it seems like the numbers on the proposed ICO rates are only going to make it worthwhile to buy with mne on the first day and all other days just easier to buy in eth?  Assuming $300 eth then:   Day 1: mne would need to be slightly less than $30 to make it worthwhile to buy some and trade that to artemine.  Day 2: slightly less than $22.50.  Day 11: less than $20. Day 20:  less than  $21.42.  Day 26: less than $22.50 per MNE  Should not the price rise to buy in with mne be less aggressive than the price rise to buy in with eth over the 5 time periods in order to provide incentive to use MNE?  More like:  D1=  10 mne     (<$30.00)  D2=  13 mne     (<$34.61) D11= 15 mne    (<$40.00) D20= 16.5 mne (<$45.45) D26= 18 mne    (<$50.00)  Not saying that mne will go to those prices, per se, but that anything under that will provide incentive for people to buy in with mne.  I think that would be good for the mne community and support price rise which is fair since many mne will be burned, reducing its supply.  I'm curious what people think about this.  Also I'm wondering what type of plans will be to market the ICO.  Minerium and Artemine as all of us here know is very innovative tech, and especially green tech in this space also, but I think it lacks exposure.  What can make it stand out from the flood of other ICO we have had this year?  Thanks in advance for your comments.

Author: MiBambino
Title: [ANN] Artemine- First Self Mining Smart Contract 2.0
Body: The reason why we pay fees on Bitcoin and other alts is because the miners need to get paid. Also, forks can happen because the miners are debating which way to go. Both these problems don't exist with self mining coins. Artemine will have a practical use because they're launching an ICO factory soon. I'm guessing you'll need to pay in ART to get access to this service, just like you need to pay MNE to use the token creation service. Other than that, the devs won't stop innovating once these services are working properly. They'll probably add ART to the MNE world app, and find other use for it
